com.mojang.serialization

Interface Decoder<A>

  • Type Parameters:
    A - The type this Decoder deserializes.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Codec<A>, PrimitiveCodec<A>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CompoundListCodec, EitherCodec, ListCodec, MapCodec.MapCodecCodec, PairCodec, UnboundedMapCodec

    public interface Decoder<A>
    Deserializes (decodes) objects of a given type from a serialized form.

    A Decoder is used to transform objects from some serialized representation to a specific type using a supplied DynamicOps. Decoders encapsulate the deserialization routine for a specific type, regardless of the input serialization form.

    Implementations of Decoder are immutable once created. The methods defined in this interface never mutate the decoder in a way visible to the outside.

    Implementation Note:
    The default methods in this interface that return decoders or map decoders wrap this decoder without adding any debugging context. These methods should be overridden if deeply nested decoders are undesirable or additional debugging context is desired.
    See Also:
    Encoder, Codec

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static interface  Decoder.Boxed<A>
      A simple decoder interface that decodes an object from a Dynamic.
      static interface  Decoder.Simple<A>
      A simple decoder interface that completely decodes an object from a Dynamic, discarding any remaining serialized data.
      static interface  Decoder.Terminal<A>
      A simple decoder interface that discards any serialized input that was not used to decode the object.

      • decode

        <T> DataResult<(A,T)> decode(DynamicOps<T> ops,
                             T input)
        Decodes an object from the specified serialized data. If decoding fails, returns an error DataResult.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of the serialized form.
        Parameters:
        ops - The DynamicOps instance defining the serialized form.
        input - The serialized data.
        Returns:
        A Pair containing the decoded object and the remaining serialized data, wrapped in a DataResult.

      • parse

        default <T> DataResult<A> parse(DynamicOps<T> ops,
                                T input)
        Decodes an object from the specified serialized data, discarding any remaining data. If decoding fails, returns an error DataResult.

        For preserving remaining serialize data, use decode(DynamicOps, Object).

        Implementation Requirements:
        The default implementation is equivalent to decode(ops, input).map(Pair::getFirst).
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of the serialized form.
        Parameters:
        ops - The DynamicOps instance defining the serialized form.
        input - The serialized data.
        Returns:
        A DataResult containing the decoded object.

      • fieldOf

        default MapDecoder<A> fieldOf(String name)
        Returns a MapDecoder that decodes objects in a record under a field with the given name. The returned MapDecoder may be used in conjunction with a partially deserialized MapLike to deserialize many different fields, all using different decoders, from a single record.
        Implementation Requirements:
        The default implementation returns a FieldDecoder wrapping this decoder.
        Parameters:
        name - The field to decode objects from.
        Returns:
        A MapDecoder that performs the same decoding as this decoder, but takes the serialized value from a record under the given field.
        See Also:
        MapLike
